==English==
===Etymology===
From the town of [[Sodom]] where the [[Bible]], in Genesis chapters 18 & 19 and elsewhere, may imply such practices (see [[sodomite#Usage notes|here]]).
{{wikipedia}}
===Noun===
'''sodomy'''
#Immorality in general.
#[[Anal]] [[sex]] (generally used only in reference to this act between two males). [[Buggery]].
#Archaic: Any of various forms of [[sexual]] [[intercourse]] held to be [[unnatural]], [[abnormal]] or [[illegal]], particularly sexual intercourse with a [[beast]].
#Archaic: [[Inhospitality]].

====Usage notes====
Although in English the sense of ''zoophilia'' is considered archaic, in other languages it is the primary sense and usage of the respective term (eg German ''Sodomie'') to mean ''anal intercourse'' is considered archaic.  Caution is therefore advised when translating into or from other languages.

